<H2 SUBJECT='Attributes setting'>Attributes setting
<I1>attribute
<P>Attributes are parameters like: colour, character font, etc. which could be
changed interactively in PAW via the commands <XPH>PICTURE/IGSET, GRAPHICS/SET</XPH> and
<XPH>GRAPHICS/OPTION</XPH>. Each attribute is linked to one or more objects
(lines, histogram, etc.). The aim of this section is to give a complete description of
the attributes available in PAW and to clarify the differences between <XPH>IGSET</XPH>, which
changes attributes at the HIGZ level, and <XPH>SET </XPH>and <XPH>OPTION</XPH>,
which act at the HPLOT level.
<I1>HPLOT
<I1>HIGZ
<I1>IGSET
<I1>SET
<I1>OPTION
<H3>IGSET
<I1>IGSET
<P>The <XPH>IGSET</XPH> command has two optional parameters:
<DL COMPACT>
<DT>CHNAME
<DD>Attribute name (four characters).
<DT>VALUE
<DD>Attribute value.
</DL>
<P>
<H4>Examples
<XMP>
PAW > <HP3>IGSET MTYP 20</HP3>       | Change the marker type to 20
</XMP>
This new marker type will be used by all subsequently commands using
the current marker type.
<XMP>
PAW > <HP3>IGSET</HP3>               | Display actual and default values of all HIGZ attributes
PAW > <HP3>IGSET *</HP3>             | Set ALL HIGZ attributes to their default values
PAW > <HP3>IGSET LWID</HP3>          | Set the GIVEN HIGZ attribute to its default value
</XMP>
