<P><XPH><F>bullet</F> FAIS, FASI, MTYP</XPH> and <XPH>LTYPE</XPH>:
Set respectively the Fill Area Interior Style, The Fill Area Style Index,
the Marker TYPe and the Line TYPe. Example:
<XMP>
PAW > <HP3>IGSET FAIS 3</HP3>      | Fill area are hatched
PAW > <HP3>IGSET FASI -101</HP3>   |   with the GKSGRAL style index -101
PAW > <HP3>IGSET MTYP 25</HP3>     | Marker type is an empty square
PAW > <HP3>IGSET LTYP 15</HP3>     | Line type is dotted
</XMP>
<I1>hatch style
<I1>fill area style index
<P>The <FIGREF REFID=FAIS page=NO> gives the available GKSGRAL fill area
styles index.
<P>In addition, HIGZ provides some portable fill area styles index coded
using three digits <XPH>ijk</XPH>:
